# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase credentials
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local`, replace the placeholder values below, then
# restart the dev server (`npm run dev`) so Vite picks up the changes.
#
#
# ── How to get your values ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard and log in (or sign up).
#   2. Click "New project", give it a name, set a database password, pick a
#      region close to your users, and click "Create new project"
#      (provisioning takes ~2 minutes).
#   3. Get your publishable key: Settings (gear icon) -> API Keys.
#         - Select the "Publishable and secret API keys" tab.
#         - If you only see legacy keys, click "Create new API keys" first
#           (this is safe and keeps your legacy keys working).
#         - Under "Publishable key", copy the "default" key (sb_publishable_...).
#   4. Get your project URL: Settings -> Integrations -> Data API.
#         - The "API URL" shown there ends in /rest/v1/, e.g.
#             https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/rest/v1/
#           Use ONLY the base part for VITE_SUPABASE_URL (drop /rest/v1/):
#             https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
#           The Supabase client adds /rest/v1/, /auth/v1/, etc. on its own.
#         - Note: this moved out of the old "Settings -> API" page. The quickest
#           alternative is the "Connect" button in the top bar, which lists both
#           the Project URL and your keys together.
#   5. Enable Email auth: Authentication -> Providers -> Email.
#
# Note: `.env.local` is gitignored, so your real credentials won't be committed.
#
# When you add a database later (e.g. a "projects" table), keep using the
# publishable key here and protect your tables with Row Level Security so the
# key is safe to ship in the browser.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your project URL, e.g. https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your-project-url

# Your publishable key, looks like: sb_publishable_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-publishable-key

# Legacy fallback (optional): if your project is still on the old keys, you can
# instead set the anon key here. The app uses PUBLISHABLE_KEY if both are set.
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend API (FastAPI)
#
# Local dev (Docker): http://localhost:8000
# Production (Render): https://sentinelai-rqpf.onrender.com
# Set VITE_API_URL in Vercel env vars to the same production URL.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
